olive oil
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
2 clove garlic
½ lemon
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet pork loin steaks
15 g butter
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Mayonnaise
1 packet Parsley

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Place peeled pumpkin pieces and garlic & herb seasoning on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat. Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic.
• Zest lemon to get a good pinch, then slice into wedges.
• In a medium bowl, combine All-American spice blend, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of pepper. Add pork loin steaks and turn to coat. Set aside.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook garlic until fragrant, 1 minute. Transfer garlic oil to a large bowl.
• To the garlic oil, add lemon zest, a squeeze of lemon juice and a pinch of salt and pepper. Stir to combine and set aside.

• Return the frying pan to high heat with the butter and a drizzle of olive oil. Cook pork until cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side. Transfer to a plate, cover and rest for 5 minutes.
• To the bowl with garlic-lemon dressing, add roasted veggies, baby leaves and shredded cabbage mix, then gently toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Slice pork.
• Divide roast pumpkin slaw between bowls. Top with All-American pork.
• Drizzle with mayonnaise and tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!